Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State has said that he would focus on the development of the state if re-elected for another term come November 16. Bello who stated this at Kabba during the APC governorship campaign rally for Kogi West senatorial district, said he would reverse the downward trend in development of the state in his second term. The governor said with the commencement of prompt payment of salary arrears, his government had also started the repositioning of the state for the better. “My government is better prepared to reverse the downward developmental forced on us by the previous administration,” he said. Bello said what the state will witness in his second term is “ease, happiness, joy and prosperity”. The Director General, Bello/Onoja campaign organization, Senator Smart Adeyemi said the senatorial axis was ready to reward the governor with their votes for his love for the zone. Adeyemi who equally comes from the zone,said the senatorial district will deliver 80 percent of the votes for the governor. Adeyemi said the governor being an Ebira man is a neighbour to Kogi West people “and Bible ordination called for a man to love his neighbour”. Youth group seeks Oshiomhole's intervention over alleged imposition of Senator Adeyemi 2019: Kogi West endorses Buhari, adopts Bello Kogi guber: Why Bello picked Onoja as running mate